	<h1 align="center">Contact 
        Information</h1>
      <h2>Adverse Event Reporting </h2>
      <p> Adverse event reports are welcome from all concerned individuals: patients, 
        parents/guardians, physicians and other health care providers, and vaccine 
        manufacturers. A copy of the VAERS reporting form and instructions for 
        how to submit it can be obtained by calling toll-free 1-800-822-7967 or 
        by toll-free fax at 1-877-721-0366. You may also submit requests to VAERS 
        via <a href="mailto:info@vaers.org%20" target="e-mail" name="e-mail">e-mail</a>. 
      <p> Submissions by mail may be sent to: 
      <p> Vaccine Adverse Event Reporting System<br>
        <GEO TYPE="US">P.O. Box 1100<br>
        Rockville, MD 20849-1100</GEO> 
      <p> For package deliveries, send to: 
      <p> Vaccine Adverse Event Reporting System<br>
        <GEO TYPE="US">8401 Colesville Road, Suite 200<br>
        Silver Spring, MD 20910</GEO> 
      <p> <a href="pdf/vaers_form.pdf" target="VAERS Form" name="VAERS Form">Download</a> 
        a copy of the VAERS form (PDF 23K).<br>
        Note: PDF files require the Adobe Acrobat Reader. 
        <!--- <p> *Check back in the coming months for online submissions through this 
        Web site.  --->
      <h3> National Vaccine Injury Compensation Program </h3>
      <p> The toll-free number for the National Vaccine Injury Compensation Program 
        is 1-800-338-2382. Call to obtain an information packet detailing filing 
        a claim, criteria for eligibility, and required documentation. For further 
        information write to: 
      <p> National Vaccine Injury Compensation Program<br>
        Parklawn Building, Room 8A-35<br>
        <GEO TYPE="US">5600 Fishers Lane<br>
        Rockville, Maryland 20857</GEO> 
      <p> Or visit the <a href="http://www.hrsa.gov/osp/vicp" target="National Vaccine Injury Compensation Program" name="National Vaccine Injury Compensation Program">National 
        Vaccine Injury Compensation Program</a> Web site. 
      <p> For information on the rules of the U.S. Court of Federal Claims, including 
        requirements for filing a petition, call 1-202-219-9657 or write to: 
      <p> US Court of Federal Claims<br>
        <GEO TYPE="US">717 Madison Place, N.W.<br>
        Washington, D.C. 20005</GEO> 
      <h3> General Vaccine Information </h3>
      <p> If you have questions about vaccines and immunization schedules, call 
        the CDC National Immunization Hotline at 1-800-232-2522 (English) or 1-800-232-0233 
        (Spanish), or visit the <a href="http://www.cdc.gov/nip" target="National Immunization Program" name="National Immunization Program">National 
        Immunization Program</a> Web site. </p>
       <p><a href="#top" name="Back to Top" title="Back to Top">Back to Top</a></p>
      </td>
